message.content: A "flat-coated retriever" is a breed of dog known for their affectionate and playful nature. They typically have a black or liver-colored coat that is dense and silky in texture. Their distinctive head features a long, slender muzzle with friendly eyes and floppy ears. Their body is muscular and well-proportioned, with a medium to large size. They are often used as hunting companions, as well as family pets because of their loyalty and obedience. Flat-coated retrievers can also be found in sporting competitions, such as agility or obedience trials. Overall, these dogs have a charming personality and an elegant appearance.
